reviews.text:
Staff is absolutely fantastic and the food is some of the best I've ever had.
Check them out! You absolutely will not regret it!

This is my first time in this place, and I must say that my first experience was absolutely exceptional. I ordered a 10-piece lemon pepper wet wings. They came out piping hot and ready.
The manager Blake had an upbeat attitude and was very pleasant as well as professional. Blake made a recommendation and I went with it and was not disappointed. I will be back and hope that this business continues the great work that they exhibited on my visit. Thanks again, and see you all soon.

Food was pretty good but the person taking orders behind the counter was extremely unprofessional! I went in to order two calzones, I was met with a man on his phone. Didn‚Äôt even look up when I approached the counter and truthfully looked annoyed. I ordered my first calzone and he said nothing, so I ordered my second calzone and the only two phrases he said was ‚Äúwill that be all‚Äù and the price. After I sat down he proceeded to get on his phone and treat the next customer the exact same way. Will not be back unless the service here changes.

I have never in my life felt the way I have in a place of service. As a local, I come here often, this is INSANE. The behavior of the staff is ridiculous. The past two times I have felt like a jobless and homeless person begging for water off of the street. After my experience tonight, I will not be back. And I will also be telling my local friends/neighbors not to attend. This place is RIDICULOUS!!! DO NOT COME IF YOU VALUE COSTUMER SERVICE!!!!!!!!!!!!!!(I enjoy the food, but not the service/cooks)

It was our first time visiting this place and we only stopped here because the Jimmy John‚Äôs next door was closed. I ordered 10 lemon pepper bone IN wings and my husband ordered 10 teriyaki boneless wings.
We also ordered the 1 pound of fries. This cost us just under $43.

Not checking before we left, we got home and I didn‚Äôt have 10 bone in wings but I received 20 lemon pepper boneLESS wings. Which is both a blessing and a curse, because I was looking forward to wet bone in wings. Then to our surprise my husband also ordered 10 piece teriyaki and receive 20pc which I would give a solid 8/10 pretty typical but tasty. The fries had a good spice but nothing out of the ordinary. The people were kind. I would just double check your orders !
